==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poet
<hw>Po"et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>po⟦eum⟧te</ets>, L. <ets>po⟦eum⟧ta</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to
make. Cf. <er>Poem</er>.]</ety> <def>One skilled in making poetry; one
who has a particular genius for metrical composition; the author of a
poem; an imaginative thinker or writer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>poet's</qex> eye, in a fine frenzy rolling,⟦br⟧
Doth glance from heaven to earth, from earth to heaven.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>poet</qex> is a maker, as the word signifies.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Poet laureate</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Laureate</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poetaster</ent>⟦br⟧
